HEADWORD: Rubato
<hw>Ru*ba"to</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[It.]</ety>
<def>Robbed; borrowed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs>\'d8<col><b>Temple rubato</b></col>. <ety>[It.]</ety>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <cd>Borrowed time; -- a term applied to a style of
performance in which some tones are held longer than their legitimate
time, while others are proportionally curtailed.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rubbage</ent>⟦br⟧
